---
title: Alfredo-Style Spaghetti with Herbed Pork plus Zucchini & Lemon
description: Alfredo sauce is a perennial favorite around here, and we’re confident our version will be a slam dunk at home. After all, with this dish’s creamy sauce, juicy pork, and tender pasta, how could it not be? You’ll toss spaghetti in a rich, creamy sauce loaded with nutty Parmesan, ground pepper, butter, and lemon for brightness. Next you’ll add cubes of Italian-seasoned seared boneless pork chop along with golden-brown zucchini for a hearty, delicious dinner idea all in one lucky bowl.
